com.cyc.base.kbtool

Interface ObjectTool

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CycObjectTool

    public interface ObjectTool
    Tools for creating simple CycObjects, such as constants and lists. To perform complex assertions, use the AssertTool. To lookup facts in the Cyc KB, use the LookupTool.
    See Also:
    AssertTool, LookupTool

      • generateDisambiguationPhraseAndTypes

        CycList generateDisambiguationPhraseAndTypes(CycList objects)
                                             throws CycConnectionException,
                                                    CycApiException
        Returns a list of disambiguation expressions, corresponding to each of the terms in the given list of objects. 
         (GENERATE-DISAMBIGUATION-PHRASES-AND-TYPES (QUOTE (#$Penguin #$PittsburghPenguins)))
 ==>
 ((#$Penguin "penguin" #$Bird "bird")
  (#$PittsburghPenguins "the Pittsburgh Penguins" #$IceHockeyTeam "ice hockey team"))
        Parameters:
        objects - the list of terms to be disambiguated
        Returns:
        a list of disambiguation expressions, corresponding to each of the terms in the given list of objects
        Throws:
        CycConnectionException - if a data communication error occurs
        CycApiException - if the api request results in a cyc server error

                          boolean bookkeeping,
                          boolean transcript)
                            throws CycConnectionException,
                                   CycConnectionException,
                                   CycApiException
        Returns a new CycConstant object using the constant name
        Parameters:
        name - Name of the constant. If prefixed with "#$", then the prefix is removed for canonical representation.

        transcript - If true, the operation(s) will be added to the transcript.
        Returns:
        a new CycConstant object using the constant name, recording bookkeeping information and archiving to the Cyc transcript
        Throws:

        CycConnectionException - if a data communication error occurs
        CycApiException - if the api request results in a cyc server error

      • makeUniqueCycConstant

        CycConstant makeUniqueCycConstant(String startName)
                                  throws CycConnectionException,
                                         CycConnectionException,
                                         CycApiException
        Returns a new unique CycConstant object using the constant start name prefixed by TMP-, recording bookkeeping information and archiving to the Cyc transcript. If the start name begins with #$ that portion of the start name is ignored.
        Parameters:
        startName - the starting name of the constant which will be made unique using a suffix.
        Returns:
        a new CycConstant object using the constant starting name, recording bookkeeping information and archiving to the Cyc transcript
        Throws:
        CycConnectionException - if cyc server host not found on the network
        CycConnectionException - if a data communication error occurs
        CycApiException - if the api request results in a cyc server error

      • makeUniqueCycConstant

        CycConstant makeUniqueCycConstant(String startName,
                                String prefix)
                                  throws CycConnectionException,
                                         CycConnectionException,
                                         CycApiException
        Returns a new unique CycConstant object using the constant start name and prefix, recording bookkeeping information and but without archiving to the Cyc transcript. If the start name begins with #$ that portion of the start name is ignored.
        Parameters:
        startName - the starting name of the constant which will be made unique using a suffix.
        prefix - the prefix
        Returns:
        a new CycConstant object using the constant starting name, recording bookkeeping information and archiving to the Cyc transcript
        Throws:
        CycConnectionException - if cyc server host not found on the network
        CycConnectionException - if a data communication error occurs
        CycApiException - if the api request results in a cyc server error
